  "riddle": "1. Track down the organization that oversees public transit in Southern Nevada. In which year did it first come into existence?\n\n2. Now, transform that year into a mathematical enigma: what is the sum of its distinct prime factors?\n\n3. Next, consider a journey where distance matters. How many yards are there in 1965 meters? \n\n4. From your previous answer, discover the largest prime factor contained in that figure.\n\n5. Seek the page dedicated to the local transit system's extensive routes. How many routes does it claim to operate?\n\n6. With your cultural travels, if you ventured 1965 kilometers, how many miles would you cover?\n\n7. Reflect on that distance: what does the sum of its digits reveal to you?\n\n8. Search for the political party guiding the Republican side in the state and unveil the name of its current chairperson.\n\n9. Welcome to the space where legislative discussions occur. What is the elevation of this assembly's headquarters?\n\n10. What figure represents the number of House of Representatives seats allocated to this state? \n\n11. Taking that total, identify the quantity of its divisors.\n\n12. As a quick detour, if you were to measure 4 kilometers, how would that convert to miles?\n\n13. Prepare for an election! How many seats in the assembly will be contested in 2024?\n\n14. Returning to the realm of distances, how many yards are there in 1965 meters?\n\n15. Onward to the Senate: what is the number of seats that will be up for election in 2024?\n\n16. Now envision the elections — what is the elevation of the site where they will unfold?\n\n17. Nearby stadiums hold tales of entertainment; how many can you find close to this election site?\n\n18. Combine your findings: what is the absolute difference between the elevation you found in clue 16 and the count of nearby stadiums in clue 17?\n\n19. The seat of governance awaits your attention. What coordinates mark the location of this legislative building?\n\n20. Elevate your curiosity: what is the elevation of the state capitol?\n\n21. As you prepare to conclude your exploration, how does the public rate the state capitol on Google?\n\n22. Combine your elevations from clue 20 with the Google rating from clue 21. What sum do you derive?\n\n23. An unexpected detour might lead you to the northern state. What elevation does a location near the legislature of that state have?\n\n24. Now set your sights on the legislative center once more. How many members are found in this assembly?\n\n25. What is the elevation of the building that houses these lawmakers?\n\n26. Nearby universities bustle with activity; how many can you count in the vicinity of this legislative building?\n\n27. Merge your results: what is the absolute difference between the elevation from clue 25 and the number of universities found in clue 26?\n\n28. Look back at the assembly count from clue 24 and find its digital root — reduce it to a single digit.\n\n29. If you look toward the northern lands, what elevation does a region known as Makrellbekken possess?\n\n30. In a different yet related sphere, find the date marking the start of the current lieutenant governor’s tenure.\n\n31. Lastly, from clues 7 and 9, compute the digital root of (5 + 2032). What final single-digit result arises from this calculation?",
